---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import SEO from "../components/SEO.astro";
---

<BaseLayout currentPath="/about/">
  <SEO
    slot="head"
    title="About China AI Tutorials"
    description="China AI Tutorials — The largest English-language resource for learning Chinese AI tools. 100 in-depth tutorials covering DeepSeek, Kimi, Qwen, Doubao, ZhipuAI, Xiaomi, Kuaishou, and more."
  />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 class="page-title">About China AI Tutorials</h1>

      <div class="prose">
        <h2>🌏 The Problem We Solve</h2>
        <p>
          Chinese AI tools — DeepSeek, Kimi (Moonshot AI), Qwen (Alibaba Cloud), Doubao (ByteDance),
          ZhipuAI, Xiaomi, Kuaishou — are advancing at an extraordinary pace. They now rival or
          exceed Western alternatives in many benchmarks, often at a fraction of the cost.
        </p>
        <p>
          But there's a problem: <strong>high-quality English tutorials and documentation for
          these tools are almost non-existent.</strong> Most official docs are Chinese-only.
          English-speaking communities have scattered, surface-level discussions at best.
          Developers who want to use these powerful tools face a massive language barrier.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>China AI Tutorials exists to fix this.</strong> We are the most comprehensive
          English-language resource for learning to use Chinese AI tools.
        </p>

        <h2>📚 What We Offer</h2>
        <div class="feature-grid">
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h3>🔬 100+ In-Depth Tutorials</h3>
            <p>Every tutorial includes runnable, complete code examples tested against actual APIs. No armchair theory — everything works on your machine.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h3>🌉 Chinese-English Bridge</h3>
            <p>We dive deep into official Chinese documentation, developer communities, and GitHub repos — then present the knowledge in fluent, idiomatic technical English.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h3>🔄 Continuously Updated</h3>
            <p>Chinese AI APIs evolve fast. Every tutorial carries a "Last updated" date, and we refresh content when APIs change, prices shift, or new features launch.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h3>⚖️ Independent & Unbiased</h3>
            <p>No sponsored content. No affiliate agenda. All model comparisons and benchmark discussions are based on real, reproducible measurements.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h3>📐 From Zero to Production</h3>
            <p>Tutorials organized by level: Beginner → Intermediate → Advanced. Whether you're writing your first API call or building a RAG pipeline, we have you covered.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h3>🌍 Open to the World</h3>
            <p>All tutorials are free. Code samples are MIT-licensed. The whole site is built as a static site for speed and accessibility.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2>🎯 Who This Is For</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Software Developers</strong> who want to integrate Chinese AI APIs into their applications.</li>
          <li><strong>AI/ML Engineers</strong> exploring cost-effective alternatives to Western LLM providers.</li>
          <li><strong>Technical Writers & Content Creators</strong> covering the global AI landscape.</li>
          <li><strong>Students & Researchers</strong> needing hands-on, practical AI tutorials.</li>
          <li><strong>Startup Founders</strong> evaluating AI infrastructure options.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>🛠 The Tech Behind This Site</h2>
        <p>
          Built with <a href="https://astro.build" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Astro</a> —
          a modern static site generator that produces near-zero JavaScript by default.
          Styled with <a href="https://tailwindcss.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Tailwind CSS</a>
          and <a href="https://daisyui.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">daisyUI</a>.
          Full-text search powered by <a href="https://pagefind.app" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Pagefind</a>.
          All content written in Markdown with code syntax highlighting via Shiki.
          Deployed on GitHub Pages with automatic CI/CD.
        </p>
        <p>
          The design follows a warm, reading-focused aesthetic inspired by high-quality
          editorial websites — cream backgrounds, serif display type, and amber accents
          that are comfortable for long reading sessions.
        </p>

        <h2>📬 Get In Touch</h2>
        <p>
          Have a tutorial idea? Found a bug? Want to collaborate?
          <a href="/contact/">Send us a message</a> or email
          <a href="mailto:xy802165@gmail.com">xy802165@gmail.com</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .section { padding: var(--space-2xl) 0; }
  .page-title { margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: var(--space-xl); }

  .prose h2 {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .prose ul {
    margin-left: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .prose li {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .feature-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-md);
    margin: var(--space-lg) 0;
  }

  .feature-card {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .feature-card h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .feature-card p {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 0;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .feature-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
